BriefingText:
BRIEFING

The primary pilot objective of the first manned orbital flight is to give detailed reporting of spacecraft system operation,

Checks:
1) Electrical check
Write down the voltage off all batteries, the main bus, and the standby bus in your notes

2) Station check
Ensure ASCS on and in retro attitude. Note the attitude, attitude rates, retrograde times, cabin pressure, temperatures, oxygen levels, fuel levels, and electrical check

3) 30 minute check
Check X,Y,Z

4) Blood pressure check
Start the blood pressure system, let it run for 30 seconds, then stop it.

Retro sequence areas
1A
1B
1C
1D
1E
1F


FLIGHT PLAN
00:07 - CONTROL SYSTEM CHECK

00:24 - 60 YAW MANEUVER

00:45 - IOS: Look for flare

180 YAW MANEUVER

STAR TRACKING CHECK
Star Tracking. From orbit attitude, the spacecraft will be pitched up approximately 34Â°. A star will be chosen which falls on the approximate center line of the window. The spacecraft will then be pitched down at a rate to hold the star in the same position relative to the window. The procedure is complete when the astronaut is satisfied with his ability to hold a star in a fixed position with respect to the spacecraft window.
Description: MA-6 will take the first american astronaut into an orbit around the Earth. It will use the new and powerful Mercury Atlas Launch Vehicle to carry the capsule up to a speed of 7800 m/s.

MissionActivities.Description: To check all the control modes in order to assure their readiness as backups to the ASCS system. This procedure will check all control modes. The spacecraft is on ASCS in orbit attitude at the beginning of the test.

Steps.Description: Set ASCS to AUX ON, RSCS to RATE COMD and MANUAL to PULL DIRECT
Push MANUAL to PUSH RATE COMD
Set ASCS to AUX ON, RSCS to RATE COMD and MANUAL to PULL DIRECT
Push MANUAL to PUSH RATE COMD
Set ASCS to AUX ON, RSCS to RATE COMD and MANUAL to PULL DIRECT
Push MANUAL to PUSH RATE COMD
Set ASCS to AUX ON, RSCS to RATE COMD and MANUAL to PULL DIRECT
Push MANUAL to PUSH RATE COMD
Set ASCS to AUX ON, RSCS to RATE COMD and MANUAL to PULL DIRECT
Push MANUAL to PUSH RATE COMD
Set ASCS to AUX ON, RSCS to RATE COMD and MANUAL to PULL DIRECT
Push MANUAL to PUSH RATE COMD
Return to normal ASCS Auto mode.

MissionActivities.Title: Control Systems Check

MissionActivities.Description: The 60Â° yaw maneuver will be used to check the periscope as a yaw reference when large angular errors exist.

Steps.Description: Set up low yaw right (2Â°/sec) rate
Allow the spacecraft to drift until the yaw angle becomes approximately 60Â°. Keep roll at 0Â°
Stabilize the spacecraft rates to zero.
Observe the motion of the ground track through the periscope on both low and high magnification.
Set up a low left yaw motion and stabilise the spacecraft attitude at 0Â° yaw, 0Â° roll, and -34Â° pitch. Use periscope for the reference.
Record results of the maneuver in Notes, and return to Orbit Attitude

MissionActivities.Title: 60Â° Yaw Maneuver

MissionActivities.Description: To determine the ability of the astronaut to control the attitude of the spacecraft using the horizon as a control reference under day and night conditions.

Steps.Description: Align the spacecraft to orbit attitude on the instruments (-34,0,0)

MissionActivities.Title: Day Horizon Check

MissionActivities.Description: To determine the ability of the astronaut to control the attitude of the spacecraft using the horizon as a control reference under day and night conditions.

Steps.Description: Align the spacecraft to orbit attitude on the instruments (-34,0,0)

MissionActivities.Title: Night Horizon Check

MissionCommands.Message: Good evening, {{profileName}} - everything seems to be in order after some delays. We are five minutes from launch, prepare the cockpit using the FINAL CHECKS checklist!
Roger, will prepare the cockpit for launch.
Use the MISSION and BRIEFING pages to get familiar with the mission.
Roger.
T-60 seconds, ensure the Launch Control is set to Ready.
Cockpit is ready for launch
T-30 seconds!
T-10 seconds!
Ignition!
Roger. The clock is operating. We're underway.
Hear loud and clear.
Roger. We're programing in roll okay.
Little bumpy around here.
Roger.
Standby for 20 seconds.
Roger.
2-- 1, mark.
Roger. Backup clock is started.
Fuel {{fuelAB}}, oxygen {{oxygenAB}}, amps {{ampsMainBus}}.
Roger. Loud and clear. Flight path is {{pitch}}.
Have some vibration area coming up here now.
Roger. Reading you loud and clear.
Roger. Coming into high Q a little bit; and a little contrail went by the window or something there.
Roger
Fuel {{fuelAB}}, oxygen {{oxygenAB}}, amps {{ampsMainBus}}. Still okay.
We're smoothing out some now, getting out of the vibration area.
Roger. You're through Max Q. Your flight path {{pitch}}
Roger. Feels good, through Max Q and smoothing out real fine.
Cabin pressure coming down by {{cabinPSI}} okay; flight very smooth now.
Sky looking very dark outside.
Cabin pressure is holding at {{cabinPSI}} okay.
Roger. Cabin pressure holding at {{cabinPSI}}.
Roger. Have had some oscillations, but they seem to be damping out okay now.
Approaching two minutes, and fuel is {{fuelAB}}, oxygen {{oxygenAB}}. The g's are building to {{g}}.
Roger. Reading you loud and clear. Flight path looking good. Pitch {{pitch}} Standby for BECO.
Roger. BECO, back to {{g}} g's.
Roger. We confirm staging on TM.
Roger.
Still have about {{g}}g's. Programming. Over.
Could see the tower go. Jettison tower is green.
Setting Auto Jettison Retro to OFF.
Setting Emergency Retro jettison Fuse switch to OFF.
Setting Retro jettison fuse to OFF.
Roger, flight path looks good.
This is {{capsuleName}}. Fuel {{fuelAB}}, oxygen {{oxygenAB}}. amps {{ampsMainBus}}.
Roger. Still reading you loud and clear. Flight path is very good. Pitch, {{pitch}}
This is {{capsuleName}}. Fuel {{fuelAB}}, oxygen {{oxygenAB}}. amps {{ampsMainBus}}.
Roger. Reading you loud and clear. {{capsuleName}}, Cape is Go; we're standing by for you.
Roger. Cape is Go and I am Go. Capsule is in good shape. Fuel {{fuelAB}}, oxygen {{oxygenAB}}, cabin pressure holding steady at {{cabinPSI}}, amps is {{ampsMainBus}}. All systems are Go.
Roger. 20 seconds to SECO.
Roger.
SECO, posigrades fired okay.
Roger.
Roger. Zero-g and I feel fine. Capsule is turning around.
Oh, that view is tremendous!
Roger. Turnaround has started.
Roger. The capsule is turning around and I can see the booster during turnaround just a couple of hundred yards behind me. It was beautiful.
Roger, {{capsuleName}}. You have a go, at least 7 orbits.
Roger. Understand Go for at least 7 orbits.
Still reading you loud and clear. Next transmission, Bermuda.
Roger. Understand next transmission, Bermuda. Capsule did damp okay and turned around. Scope has extended, okay.
{{capsuleName}}, please perform an electrical check on all batteries, and the ORBIT checklist
Roger, will perform the electrical check and the ORBIT checklist.
This is very comfortable at Zero-g. I have nothing but very fine feeling. It just feels very normal and very good.
{{capsuleName}}. Standby for retrosequence times.
Roger, ready to copy.
Roger. 1 Bravo is 00 plus 17 plus 50.
Orbit period is {{period}}, end of orbit is at {{endOfOrbitTime}}.
Your apogee altitude is {{ap}}, are you starting your control systems check?
Roger. As soon as we get done with this transmission. I understand am I cleared to control systems check? My fuel is at {{fuelAB}}
Roger, cleared for Control Systems Check. Over.
Control Systems Check is over,

Canary, {{capsuleName}}. Roger. Control check complete. Capsule in ASCS and holding. I have booster in sight out the window. It's probably about 1 mile away and going down under my position and a little bit to my left. Over.
Roger {{capsuleName}}. I read you loud and clear. Would you give me your fuel on your control systems check?
Roger, fuel at {{fuelAB}} after Control Systems Check.
Roger, please perform the CYI station check.
Roger.
{{capsuleName}}. This is Canary CapCom. Please to a blood pressure check, repeat blood pressure check.
Roger, will do the blood pressure check. [press the START blood pressure button, let it run for 30 seconds, then press STOP]
This is {{capsuleName}}. Have beautiful view of the African Coast, both in the scope, and out the window. Out the window is by far the best view.
Roger, I read you. We're getting the blood pressure now.
Blood pressure received, your blood pressure is {{bloodStatus}}
Please stand by for KNO.
{{capsuleName}}, this is Kano Cap Com, I read you loud and clear. How do you read me? Over.
Kano Cap Com, loud and clear. Will do a quick station check. Over.
This is {{capsuleName}}, starting 60Â° yaw maneuver. I'm about 40 seconds late on that one. Starting yaw maneuver at present time. Over.
Roger, starting 60Â° Yaw Maneuver activity.
60Â° Yaw Maneuver over.
Roger. You want to stand by for retrosequence time, Area 1 Charlie?
I will broadcast this time in the blind for Area l Charlie, 00 32 12, 00 32 12.
00 32 22. Is that affirm? Over. Standing by for ZZB
This is {{capsuleName}}. Hello, Zanzibar, {{capsuleName}}. Do you receive? Over.
{{capsuleName}}, {{capsuleName}}, this is Zanzibar Corn Tech transmitting on HF, UHF, do you copy? Over.
I copy, will do the 30 minutes check and a blood check. Over [perform another blood check]
Blood check received, blood status is {{bloodStatus}}.
{{capsuleName}}. Are you ready to copy your Contingency Area 1 Delta retrosequenee time? Over.
Roger. Say 1 Delta.
1 Delta is 00 50 24. Did you copy? Over.
Roger. 00 50 24 for 1 Delta.
Roger. Stand by for IOS in a few minutes.
Hello, {{capsuleName}}. {{capsuleName}}, IOS Corn Teeh. Over.
Hello, IOS Corn Teeh, {{capsuleName}}. Had a beautiful sunset and can see the light way out almost up to the northern horizon.
Roger.You have 1 Delta retrosequence times? I have areas 1 Echo, Foxtrot, and Hotel. Are you prepared to copy?
All right, go ahead with retrotimes. Over.
Roger. Area 1 Echo is one hour, 15 minutes, 42 seconds. I say again, one hour, 15 minutes, 42 seconds. Over.
Roger. One Echo is 01 plus 15 plus 42.
Roger. Area Foxtrot is one hour, 28 minutes, 50 seconds. I say again, one hour, 28 minutes, 50 seconds.
Roger. Foxtrot is 01 plus 28 plus 50.
That is affirmative.
Area Hotel is four hours, 32 minutes, 42 seconds. Four hours, 32 minutes, 42 seconds. Over.
Roger. 04 plus 32 plus 42.
Roger. That is affirmative. Over.
We have been advised that the flare has been ignited. Do you see anything? Over.
This is {{capsuleName}}. Negative. I don't have anything in the scope or out the window.
Roger, understand. Do you have any feelings from weightlessness? Over.
This is Friendship Seven. Negative, I feel fine so far. Over.
Roger, stand by for MUC.
{{capsuleName}}, Muchea Com Tech. We read you. Would you.
Hello, Muchea Corn Tech. This is {{capsuleName}}, reading you loud and clear. How me?
Please make note of any star, weather or landmark observations. Have you seen anything special?

Roger. The stars I can see through it as they go down toward the real horizon, but it is a very visible single band or layer pretty well up above the normal horizon. Sunset was beautiful, and went down quite fast. Over.
Roger. Shortly you may observe some lights down there. You want to take a check on that to your right? Over.
That was about the shortest day I've ever run into. Roger, will check for lights as I come closer to the coast.
Short day, yes. Kinda passes rapidly, huh. Roger.
Roger. I do have the lights in sight on the ground. Over.
Just to my right I can see a big pattern of lights apparently right on the coast. I can see the outline of a town and a very bright light just to the south of it.
Perth and Rockingham, you're seeing there.
Roger. The lights show up very well and thank everybody for turning them on, will you?
We sure will, {{profileName}}
Stand by for WOM
{{capsuleName}}, {{capsuleName}}. This is Woomera Cap Com, reading you loud and clear. We have TM solid. Woomera standing by.
Roger, Woomera.
How do you feel {{profileName}}?

I have had no ill effects at all as yet from any zero-g. It's very pleasant, in fact. Visual acuity is still excellent. No astigmatic effects. Head movements caused no nausea or discomfort whatsoever. Over.
Roger. Please proceed with 30 minute check and night observations. Stand by for CANTON.
Friendship Seven. This is Canton Com Tech. Do you read? Over.
This is {{capsuleName}}. Loud and clear.

This is {{capsuleName}}. I'll try to describe what I'm in here. I am in a big mass of some very small particles, that are brilliantly lit up like they're luminescent. I never saw anything like it. They round a little; they're coming by the capsule, and they look like little stars. A whole shower of them coming by.
Roger, {{capsuleName}}. Can you hear any impact with the capsule? Over.
Negative, negative. I noticed them at 01 15. Standing by for GYM.
Hello, Guaymas Com Tech, Guaymas Com Tech. This is {{capsuleName}}.
This is {{capsuleName}}. Just as the sun came up, there were some brilliantly lighted particles that looked luminous, that were swirling around the capsule. Over.
{{capsuleName}}, Guaymas. Prepare to copy retrosequence times for Areas 2 Alpha, Golf, hotel.
This is {{capsuleName}}, ready to copy.
Area 2 Alpha 01 36 38. Area Golf 03 00 41.
Roger, Area Golf is 03 plus 00 plus 41. Is that affirm?
That's affirmative. Area Hotel is 04 32 40.
Roger, 04 plus 32 plus 40 for Hotel. Over.
This is {{capsuleName}}. Yaw is drifting out of orbit attitude and will bring it back in. Over.
Roger, slight drift to the right in Yaw. Try to see if it maintains in different flightmodes.
Roger, will try different flight modes.
Any updates on the yaw drift? If it's still there, we suggest you fly in FBW or in Manual flight, and maintain desired attitude yourself.
Roger.
{{capsuleName}}, can you give us an update of the issues you are having with the ASCS?

I will use fly-by-wire so I can control more accurately. It just started as I got to Guaymas, and appears to be it drifts off in yaw, to the right at about 1Â° per second. Will use fly-by-wire and controlling manually. Over.
Roger. Understand. Do you have a retrofire time for 2 Bravo and 2 Charlie?
This is {{capsuleName}}. Negative.
OK, 2 Bravo, 01 50 00; 2 Charlie, 02 05 59. Over.
Ah, this is {{capsuleName}}. Understand 1 Bravo is 01 plus 50 plus 00; 2 Charlie, correction 2 Bravo is 01 50 00, 2 Charlie is 02 plus 05 plus 59.
That is affirmative. Standby one, please.
This is {{capsuleName}}. What appears to have happened is, I believe, I have no one pound thrust in left yaw. So it drifts over out of limits and then hits it with the high thrust. Over.
Roger, {{capsuleName}}, we concur here. Recommending you remain fly-by-wire.
Please perform the 30 minute check and stand by for CYI. Over.
Hello, Canary. Friendship Seven. Receive you loud and a little garbled. Do you receive me? Over.
{{capsuleName}}, {{capsuleName}}, this is CYI. We are reading you loud and clear; we are reading you loud and clear. CYI.
I am instructed to ask you to correlate the actions of the particles surrounding your spacecraft with the actions of your control jets. Do you read? Over.
This is {{capsuleName}}. I do not think they were from my control jets, negative. Over.
Roger, I understand. Your medical report is excellent.
This is {{capsuleName}}. The sun coming through the window is very warm where it hits the suit. I get quite a bit of heat from it.
Roger. Please start the Day Horizon Check. Over.
Roger, will start the Day Horizon Check. Over.
Activity over. Standing by for ATS. Over.
Hello, ATS Cap Com. Read you loud and clear.
Please initiate a yaw to 180 degrees, and maintain forward looking flight formation using FBW or MP. Over.
Roger, going 180 degrees.
Roger, please maintain 180 degrees yaw and return to normal orbital attitude before reaching KNO.
Roger, will maintain forward looking attitude until KNO.
{{capsuleName}}, how do you read?
I read you loud and clear, how me?
I read you loud and clear, how did you like the forward facing attitude?
I like to forward-facing attitude much better, over.
Roger, please start the pre-dark checklist as soon as you loose contact with us.
Roger, will do the pre-dark checklist. I will cut automatic yaw and see if it fixes the yaw drift. Over
Standing by for IOS
{{capsuleName}}, {{capsuleName}} this is IOS, transmitting on HF UHF. Do you read? Over.
IOS, this is Friendship Seven. Over.
What is your status?
Still having drift in the yaw, correcting manually. Other systems seem to work well.
Roger, please proceed with your 30 minute check. Over.
Roger.
I read you okay, Indian Com Tech. This is {{capsuleName}}. I'm on straight manual control at present time. Fuel is at {{fuelAB}}. Over.
Please perform a Night Horizon Check, are you able to reference the horizon the same way as during the day?
That is affirmative. We have message from MCC for you to keep your Landing Bag switch in the OFF position, Landing Bag switch in off [middle] position. Over.
Roger. Landing Bag set to OFF.
Roger. Do you have Area 2 Delta time, Area 2 Delta? Over.
Negative.
Roger. Area 2 Delta time is 2 hours, 38 minutes, 31 seconds. I say again, 2 hours, 38 minutes, 31 seconds. Over.
Area 2 Echo is 2 hours plus 48 minutes plus 59 seconds.
2 hours plus 48 minutes plus 59 seconds for 2 Echo.
Roger. End of orbit area Golf is 3 hours plus 00 minutes plus 39 seconds, I say again, 3 hours plus 00 minutes plus 39 seconds. Over.
Roger, 03 plus 00 plus 39 seconds.
Roger, that is affirmative. Have you noticed any constellations yet? Over. Stand by for MUC.
{{capsuleName}}, {{capsuleName}}, this is Muchea Com Tech. Friendship Seven, this is Muchea Com Tech. Do you read?
Hello, Muchea Com Tech, {{capsuleName}}. Over.
{{capsuleName}}, please go ahead with the STAR TRACKING procedure. Over
Roger, will perform the STAR TRACKING procedure [See briefing page on this optional task].
Will you confirm the Landing Bag switch is in the off position? Over.
That is affirmative. I set the Landing Bag switch is in the center OFF position.
You haven't had any banging noises or anything of this type at higher rates?
Negative.
Roger, they wanted that answer. Please stand by for WOM.
Roger, Woomera.
{{capsuleName}}, please send us another blood test, and do the 30 minutes check. Over. [Do another blood test procedure]
Roger, blood test complete. Over
{{capsuleName}}, receiving the data now. Your blood values are {{bloodStatus}}. Please confirm your yaw drift issue. Over
The Yaw is still drifting. I have tried different flight modes, but it still drifting. Over
Roger, please stand by for CTN.
{{capsuleName}}, Canton Com Tech.
Hello Canton Com Tech. {{capsuleName}}. How did you receive? Over.
{{capsuleName}}, Canton Com Tech. Reading you loud and clear. Standby for Cap Com.
Roger. Canton Cap Com, {{capsuleName}}. Fuel {{fuelAB}}, oxygen {{oxygenAB}}, amps {{ampsMainBus}}. My condition is good. The sunrise is coming around the capsule. Over.
Roger, {{capsuleName}}. This is Canton. We have TM solid; go ahead, Over.
This is {{capsuleName}}, and now that the sunrise is starting, I have all these little particles coming around the capsule again, just at sunrise.
Roger, {{capsuleName}}.
All these little particles; there are thousands of them; and they're not coming from the capsule. They're something that's already up there because they're all over the sky.
{{capsuleName}}, this is Canton. Our Aeromed would like to hear any comments you have on weightlessness, nausea, dizziness, taste and smell sensations. Over.
This is {{capsuleName}}, I have no sensations at all from weightlessness except very pleasant. No ill effects at all, I'm not sick; feel fine. I have had no dizziness.
I've been mainly concerned with this control problem. Over.
Roger
{{capsuleName}}, this in Canton. We also have no indication that your landing bag might be deployed. Over.
Roger. Did someone report landing bag could be down? Over.
Negative, we had a request to monitor this and to ask you if you heard any flapping, when you had high capsule rates.
Negative. Standing by for HAW
{{capsuleName}}, Hawaii Com Tech on UHF and HF. How do you read? Over.
Hello Hawaii. Loud and clear. Over.
What is your status, over.
Still haivng issues with Yaw, and the attitude seems to have drifted a bit.
If you feel like it, you can try to cage and uncage the gyros to realign with the horizon. [optional, advanced] You can use the window and the scope to see drift.
Roger, I will consider it.
I'll give you 3 Alpha if you're ready to copy.
Roger, ready to copy 3 Alpha.
Roger. 3 Alpha is 03 plus 11 plus 26. Over.
Do you consider youself GO for another orbit?
Roger, I'm GO for another orbit.
Roger, ground concur.
Please go ahead with ground observations over mainland. Over. Standby for CNV,
Canaveral Com Tech. How do you copy? Over.
Hello, Cap Com. {{capsuleName}}. Fuel is {{fuelAB}}; oxygen is {{oxygenAB}}; amps {{ampsMainBus}}. Over.
{{capsuleName}}, reading you loud and clear. I'll give you the 3 Bravo Time, 03 22 26. Over.
Roger, 03 22 26, for 3 Bravo
3 Charlie, 03 40 18. Over.
Roger, 03 40 18 for 3 Charlie.

That is correct. At this time change your retro setting manually to 04 32 38. [Pull the lever under the clock down so the lever marker is on the first upper MIN marker, the time will adjust, then put it back to middle position when time is set]
Roger. Will do this now.

Roger. We recommend for the third orbit that you use gyros as you desire either normal or free so that in the event prior to retrofire on the third orbit that the scanners and ASCS do not program properly you may use your gyros in the free position for attitude reference. Over.
Let the gyros work in the free position if you desire. Over.
Roger
Also, we recommend that you allow the capsule to drift on manual conuol in order to conserve fuel. Over.
Roger. Standing by for BDA.
{{capsuleName}}, Bermuda Cap Com.
Go ahead, Bermuda.
Cape recommends that you reenter on ASCS with manual for backup.
Roger, this is {{capsuleName}}. Understand recommend ASCS with manual backup.
Affirmative.
Fuel at {{fuelAB}}, oxygen at {{oxygenAB}}.
Roger. Stand by for IOS
{{capsuleName}}, {{capsuleName}}, this is Indian Cap Com on UHF. Do you read? Over.
Indian Cap Com, loud and clear.
Please maintain retro attitude using ASCS or the flight mode of your desire. Over.
Roger.
I have your retrosequence times. Are you prepared to copy? Over.
{{capsuleName}}. Go ahead.
Roger. Area 3 Delta, Area 3 Delta is 4 hours, 12 minutes, 3 seconds.
Area 3 Delta is 04 plus 12 plus 32. Is that affirm?
Affirmative. Area 3 Echo, Area 3 Echo is 4 hours, 22 minutes, 12 seconds. I say again; 4 hours, 22 minutes, 12 seconds. Over.
Roger. Area 3 Echo is 04 plus 22 plus 12.
Roger. Area Hotel is 4 hours, 32 minutes, 38 seconds. Say it again; 4 hours, 32 minutes 38 seconds. Over.
Roger. 04 plus 32 plus 38.
That is affirmative. Stand by for MUC.
Hello, Muchea Com Tech. I read you loud and clear.
Roger, read you loud and clear, please perform a 30 minute check. Over
This is {{capsuleName}}. In 45 more seconds I would like to have you send a message for me, please. Over.

I want you to send a message to the Director, to the Commandant, U.S. Marine Corps, Washington. Tell him I have my 4 hours required flight time in for the month and request flight chit be established for me. Over.
Roger. Will do.  Think they'll pay it?
I don't know. Gonna find out
Roger. Is this flying time or rocket time?
Lighter than air, buddy.
Rog. Please maintain orbit attitude or as near orbit attitude as possible before retrofire sequence. Over
Roger. Standing by for WOM
Friendship Seven, Woomera Cap Com. We have contact UHF and TM solid. Surgeon recommends that if you haven't eaten that you eat in the near future.
Roger. I see those particles again. Over.
Roger. Please cross check your orbit attitude and drift with the periscope and window and perform the PRE-RETRO checklist, stand by for HAW.

{{capsuleName}}, we have been reading an indication on the ground of segment 51, which is Landing Bag Deploy. We suspect this is a erroneous signal. However, Cape would like, you to check this by putting the Landing Bag switch in auto position? Do you concur with this? Over.
Roger, setting landing bag to AUTO.
Roger, that's fine. In this case, we'll go ahead, and the reentry sequence will be normal.
Roger, reentry sequence will be normal.
{{capsuleName}}, have you completed your pre-retro check list?
Roger. Standing by for mainland, will prepare for retro sequence.
Leave yom retropack on through your pass over Texas. Do you read?
Roger. Standing by for retro sequence.
Roger, retro sequence is green.
You have a green. Keep your attitude in green. Over.
Roger, retros are firing.
Sure, they be.
Are they ever. It feels like I'm going back toward Hawaii.
Don't do that, you want to go to the East Coast.
Keep your retro pack on until you pass Texas.
Consideration about leaving retropack on, they will inform you over Texas.
Roger.
This is Texas Cap Corn, Friendship Seven. We are recommending that you leave the retropackage on through the entire reentry. This means that you will have to override the 0.05g switch at our MARK.
This is {{capsuleName}}. What is the reason for this? Do you have any reason? Over.
Not at this time; this is the judgment of Cape Flight.
Roger. Say again your instructions please. Over.
We are recommending that the retropackage not, I say again, not be jettisoned. This means that you will have to override the 0.05g switch. We will notify you when you will have to override.
Roger. Going to reentry attitude in that case.
We are not sure whether or not your landing bag has deployed. We feel it is possible to reenter with the retropackage on. We see no difficulty at this time in that type of reentry. Over.
Roger, understand.
Please override .05g now, over.
I can feel the Gs over.
Going through heavy G load, over.
80000 feet now. Do you read?
Seven, this is Cape. What's your general condition? Are you feeling pretty well?
My condition is good, but that was a real fireball, boy. Will perform LANDING checklist. Over.
Roger. Pay attention to drogue and chute deplay, override if nessecary. Over.
Is the drogue holding all right?
Roger, the drogue looks good.
Main chute in on green. Chute is out at 10,800 feet and beautiful chute. Chute looks good. On O2 emergency and the chute looks very good.
Roger, we have you in visual.
Roger, standing by for impact.
This is Cape. Do you have the Landing Bag on green? Over.
{{capsuleName}}. Impact. Rescue Aids is manual.
Roger, welcome home. Pickup in under way. Over.
Roger. It is extremely warm in the capsule. Over.

Title: Mercury-Atlas 6
